BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.69539 Tw (Access-based control models were designed for simpler systems. They assume stable roles, predictable) Tj T* 0 Tw .424975 Tw (actions, limited system autonomy, and clear boundaries between user and system. These assumptions held) Tj T* 0 Tw .247816 Tw (reasonably well in environments where a person sat at a terminal, initiated an action, waited for a result, and) Tj T* 0 Tw (reviewed it before proceeding. That environment no longer describes how most automated systems operate.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 506.2921 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 86.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL -0.10264 Tw (Modern automated systems include dynamic decision-making that adapts to incoming data without waiting for) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.72136 Tw (human instruction. They involve continuous updates that change system behaviour between the point of) Tj T* 0 Tw .539449 Tw (access and the point of action. They exhibit adaptive behaviour that may produce outputs not anticipated at) Tj T* 0 Tw .670514 Tw (the time permissions were assigned. They operate across distributed processes that span multiple systems) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.671079 Tw (and jurisdictions. And they initiate indirect actions triggered by system logic \227 actions that no individual) Tj T* 0 Tw (explicitly requested, but that the system was implicitly permitted to take by virtue of prior access.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 430.9535 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .147574 Tw (Under these conditions, access becomes insufficient as a control mechanism. A system may act on behalf of) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.800289 Tw (a user, make recommendations that influence decisions, trigger downstream processes automatically, or) Tj T* 0 Tw .694549 Tw (operate across multiple connected systems. Once access is granted, actions can propagate far beyond the) Tj T* 0 Tw (original intent of the person who granted it.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 339.615 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL -0.098701 Tw (Without control at the point of action, systems can execute unintended operations without anyone recognising) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.598406 Tw (that the original intent has been exceeded. They can escalate behaviour without review, expanding their) Tj T* 0 Tw .473445 Tw (scope incrementally until they are operating well beyond what was originally authorised. And they can apply) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.487799 Tw (decisions at scale without verification \227 repeating the same flawed condition across thousands of cases) Tj T* 0 Tw (before anyone has the opportunity to question whether it was valid in any of them.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 248.2764 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.26798 Tw (At small scale, this gap is tolerable. At large scale, it becomes dangerous. Because automation does not) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.631355 Tw (stop. It repeats. It amplifies. It applies the same condition across thousands of cases. A single incorrect) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.102324 Tw (assumption made at the point of access becomes thousands of incorrect actions at execution. That is the) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.340549 Tw (failure multiplier \227 and it operates silently, within normal system parameters, until the accumulated harm) Tj T* 0 Tw (becomes undeniable.) Tj T* ET
Q
