BT 1 0 0 1 0 86.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .743105 Tw (In poorly governed systems, these two conditions become aligned \227 implicitly or explicitly. If a system has) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.735273 Tw (the technical capability to perform an action, it is treated as though it is also allowed to perform it. The) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.978406 Tw (capability itself becomes the justification. This is a fundamental governance failure. It means that every) Tj T* 0 Tw .960549 Tw (expansion of system capability is automatically an expansion of system authority \227 without any deliberate) Tj T* 0 Tw .747975 Tw (decision, without any human confirmation, and without any assessment of whether the expanded capability) Tj T* 0 Tw (should be permitted.) Tj T* ET
