BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .440512 Tw (In these scenarios, systems may operate correctly according to their logic \227 following their rules, producing) Tj T* 0 Tw .433299 Tw (their outputs, executing their functions \227 but incorrectly according to real-world expectations. The system is) Tj T* 0 Tw .855734 Tw (doing what it was designed to do. What it was not designed to do is check whether it should. This creates) Tj T* 0 Tw .051012 Tw (misalignment between technical correctness and operational validity \227 a gap that neither the system nor any) Tj T* 0 Tw (oversight layer is positioned to close, because the missing control point is inside the execution loop itself.) Tj T* ET
