BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .742511 Tw (As systems scale, authority must scale with them. This does not mean increasing manual intervention \227 a) Tj T* 0 Tw .205299 Tw (requirement for human confirmation at every action would eliminate the efficiency benefits of automation and) Tj T* 0 Tw .336012 Tw (is not a realistic governance model for large-scale systems. The requirement is more precise: authority must) Tj T* 0 Tw (be designed to scale, not assumed to extend automatically as systems grow.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 425.8031 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 118.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .542418 Tw (Scalable authority requires that authority rules be defined clearly \227 so that the conditions for valid authority) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.458279 Tw (are explicit and consistent regardless of the volume of actions being processed. It requires that authority) Tj T* 0 Tw .88387 Tw (checks be automated where appropriate \227 so that validation occurs at execution without requiring manual) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.127712 Tw (review of every individual action. It requires that escalation pathways exist \227 so that when automated) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.488477 Tw (validation cannot confirm authority, the system has a defined mechanism for escalating to human review) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.33512 Tw (rather than defaulting to continuation. And it requires that human oversight be maintained for high-impact) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.760412 Tw (actions \227 where the consequence of acting without confirmed authority is too significant to leave to) Tj T* 0 Tw (automated validation alone.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 334.4646 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .913129 Tw (Without scalability, systems encounter two failure modes. They either become inefficient through too much) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.072437 Tw (manual control \227 creating bottlenecks that defeat the purpose of automation and incentivise workarounds) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.098023 Tw (that undermine governance. Or they become uncontrolled through too little authority validation \227 operating at) Tj T* 0 Tw .964912 Tw (scale without any meaningful check at the point of action, and amplifying whatever conditions are present,) Tj T* 0 Tw (correct or otherwise.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 259.126 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.714442 Tw (Scale without authority produces uncontrolled amplification \227 the system grows, but so does the failure) Tj T* 0 Tw .952591 Tw (condition. Scale with authority produces controlled expansion \227 the system grows within governance, and) Tj T* 0 Tw .367679 Tw (the failure condition is constrained by the authority model at every level. That difference determines whether) Tj T* 0 Tw (systems stabilise or collapse under their own behaviour as complexity increases.) Tj T* ET
